A Vulkan-based translation layer for Direct3D 10/11 which allows running 3D applications on Linux using Wine.

== Installation ==
{{important| DXVK is not in gentoo repo nor gentoo overlay, must be compiled from source.}}

Upstream instructions: https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk

1. '''Download from a source.'''<br />
https://github.com/doitsujin/dxvk

2. '''Install dependencies.'''<br />
- wine 3.10 or newer<br />
- Meson build system (at least version 0.43)<br />
- MinGW64 compiler and headers (requires threading support)<br />
- glslang compile<br />
- app-emulation/winetricks-9999<br />

3. '''Wineprefix'''<br />
Set $WINEPREFIX to your .wine which is located in $HOME/.wine by default.
{{Cmd|export WINEPREFIX{{=}}/path/to/.wine-prefix}}

Invoke echo for verification if desired.
{{Cmd|echo "$WINEPREFIX"}}

4. '''Unpack source'''<br />
Unpack source to a `~/.dxvk`.
{{Cmd|./package-release.sh master /home/$USER/.dxvk --no-package}}

5. '''Installation'''<br />
Make winetricks do the installation by invoking
{{Cmd|winetricks --force setup_dxvk.verb}}

